summary:
You may have enabled and configure BitLocker for silent encryption on your Windows 10 Autopilot joined devices, but have you had the headache of devices that don&rsquo;t have a Windows Recovery Environment (WinRE) configured? Yep? Me too&hellip;
What you&rsquo;ll see in either the Bitlocker-API event log, or within the Encryption Readiness reporting in Endpoint Manager the following, glorious error:
The OS volume is unprotected | Windows Recovery Environment (WinRE) isn't configured

